The former Prime Minister of Denmark Helle Thorning-Schmidt has turned helping Ukraine into a competition on tonight's "Ukraine Special" episode of Question Time. Addressing Nadhim Zahawi, she said: "You said something that almost made me chuckle before when you said that Putin will think that the UK is leading the efforts against Russia right now. Of course it's not. The European Union is leading the effort against Russia! So I don't think they will see Boris Johnson as a particular leader in this." THIS LIVE BLOG IS NOW CLOSED - READ COVERAGE BELOW...